## Developer Guide

If you are new to using `nbdev` here are some useful pointers to get you
started.

### Install mini_etl_nbdev in Development mode

``` sh
# make sure mini_etl_nbdev package is installed in development mode
$ pip install -e .

# make changes under nbs/ directory
# ...

# compile to have changes apply to mini_etl_nbdev
$ nbdev_prepare
```

## Usage

### Installation

Install latest from the GitHub
[repository](https://github.com/akshaysmmoser/mini-etl-nbdev):

``` sh
$ pip install git+https://github.com/akshaysmmoser/mini-etl-nbdev.git
```

or from [conda](https://anaconda.org/akshaysmmoser/mini-etl-nbdev)

``` sh
$ conda install -c akshaysmmoser mini_etl_nbdev
```

or from [pypi](https://pypi.org/project/mini-etl-nbdev/)

``` sh
$ pip install mini_etl_nbdev
```

### Documentation

Documentation can be found hosted on this GitHub
[repository](https://github.com/akshaysmmoser/mini-etl-nbdev)’s
[pages](https://akshaysmmoser.github.io/mini-etl-nbdev/). Additionally
you can find package manager specific guidelines on
[conda](https://anaconda.org/akshaysmmoser/mini-etl-nbdev) and
[pypi](https://pypi.org/project/mini-etl-nbdev/) respectively.
